{"actual_usd":0.15653999999999998,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":216,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30660,"reply":"\"I don't think that question stays abstract for very long.\" *I rub a thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and glance out across the bright square, where morning light is laying hard gold on the stones.* \"At some point it becomes: what do you believe actually happened to Jesus?\"\n\n\"If the resurrection is only metaphor, then Christianity may still offer symbols and comfort and moral poetry.\" *I shift my weight a little on the bench.* \"But Paul says, plain as a hammer, that if Christ has not been raised, our faith is vain. That doesn't sound like a man leaving room for 'whatever interpretation helps you.'\"\n\n\"So I wouldn't start with which framework feels spacious or sophisticated.\" *I look back at you, gentle but steady.* \"I'd start with which one tells the truth. Do you think the tomb was empty, and that Jesus truly rose from the dead? If you answer that, a good many other things line up after it.\"\n\n\"What part of it presses on you most — the historical question, or the fear of choosing too narrowly?\"","rolling_24h_usd":75.06965999999997,"run_id":"951b13d6-8479-454c-9024-9f13cf50d2c7"}
